programme.desc: Why do zebras have stripes? How do penguins see underwater? And why are a tree frog's eyes red? In this exploration of sight, discover how some animals have evolved to see extremely well while others have evolved to be nearly invisible.

programme.title: Mysteries Of Evolution
programme.desc: Cooperation comes in many forms. Some animals cooperate to be social while others put the welfare of the group above their own reproductive potential. See the many ways species have evolved to work with one another in order to survive.

programme.title: Mysteries Of Evolution
programme.desc: Some call them "living fossils," but that's just another way to say survivors. From the shark to the horseshoe crab, these animals' early adaptations were a success, leaving them relatively unchanged for millions of years.

programme.title: Strange Creatures
programme.desc: In nature, the right stench can mean the difference between life or death. Meet nature's odor-equipped inhabitants, from vomiting grasshoppers to dung-flinging hippos, and even a flower that's adapted to smell like death.

programme.title: Strange Creatures
programme.desc: One uses a mustache to attract mates and another has a bill so big, it needs special vertebrae to carry it. Learn how nature's flying iconoclasts have evolved their appearance in order to survive.

programme.title: Strange Creatures
programme.desc: Gawk at some of the world's ugliest animals who owe their survival to the adaptations that made them so strange. A pudgy wolf eel, naked mole rat, and hideous sea lamprey may be superficially grotesque, but they're evolutionarily amazing.

programme.title: Strange Creatures
programme.desc: Witness the tiny creatures that make us squirm while hiding admirable survival skills. From playing dead, removing a tail, or being able to lift objects 30 times their weight, these insects conquer the world with their amazing adaptations.

programme.title: Strange Creatures
programme.desc: Are they guinea pigs, beavers, or something else? Capybaras embody the features of several different animals at once, as do warthogs, anteaters, and other fascinating genetic hybrids. Learn why these wannabes display such particular physical traits.

programme.title: Strange Creatures
programme.desc: The animal kingdom is filled with mimicry, transformation, and trickery. Discover how stick bugs, lion fish, emperor scorpions, and chameleons use camouflage and confusion to deceive.

programme.title: Strange Creatures
programme.desc: T-Rex and chickens seem to be as different as they can be, but they more in common that you might think. Recent research reveals that some of our favourite dinosaurs were very birdlike, and that birds are an extant kind of dinosaurs.

programme.title: Strange Creatures
programme.desc: Keep your distance from these natural-born killers. Armed with venom and other poisonous tools that make hunting easier (and escape impossible), nudibranches, cuttlefish, giant centipedes, and assassin bugs are all dressed to kill.

programme.title: Undiscovered Vistas

programme.title: Arabian Seas

programme.title: A nap hőse (?)
programme.desc: Nem csak idősebb korunkra válhatunk példaképpé, sokan már tizenévesen azok lesznek! A DIGI Sport minisorozata olyan fiatal tehetségeket mutat be, akik teljesítményükkel, eredményeikkel kiemelkednek a kortársaik közül. A minisorozat különálló, 5-7 perces epizódjaiban ilyen fiatalokról láthatnak portrékat a nézőink. Az egyes portrékban bemutatjuk a főszereplőt, megismerjük a sportágát, megkérdezzük tapasztalatairól, bemutatjuk az eddig elért eredményeit, megmutatjuk környezetét, betekintünk edzéseire, megismerjük és meghallgatjuk az edzőjét és akár hozzátartozóit, családját is.

programme.title: S.E.F.T. (?)
programme.desc: A DIGI Sport új, napi rendszerességgel jelentkező magazinműsora komoly küldetéssel indul útjára. A műsorban nagyító alá vesszük a szereplők általános szemléletmódját, táplálkozását, sportolási szokásait, valamint ellessük apró praktikáikat, amelyekkel be tudják illeszteni a sportos, egészséges és fitt, azaz a #sefter életmódot rohanó hétköznapjaikba.

programme.title: A nap hőse (?)
programme.desc: Nem csak idősebb korunkra válhatunk példaképpé, sokan már tizenévesen azok lesznek! programme.title: Hip Show
programme.desc: Hip Show takes combat sports to a whole new level. The fights are 2-on-2 (two teams of two fighters each) in a 3D 12x12 meters arena rather than inside a conventional flat ring. If one of the team members in the arena drops out after a knockout, the fight continues in a 2 versus 1 format. If the remaining team member can hold out for 60 seconds, the bout ends in a tie.

programme.title: Hip Show
programme.desc: Hip Show takes combat sports to a whole new level. The fights are 2-on-2 (two teams of two fighters each) in a 3D 12x12 meters arena rather than inside a conventional flat ring. If one of the team members in the arena drops out after a knockout, the fight continues in a 2 versus 1 format. If the remaining team member can hold out for 60 seconds, the bout ends in a tie.
